**

04:14.788 --> 04:20.127
**

04:20.160 --> 04:25.599
**

04:25.633 --> 04:27.668
[Baby fussing]

04:27.701 --> 04:31.372
**

04:32.540 --> 04:34.542
Hey, do you have
a cigarette?

04:34.575 --> 04:35.876
Liz: No. Sorry.

04:35.909 --> 04:40.648
You got like $1 so I can
get a taco or something?

04:40.681 --> 04:42.650
Uh...

04:42.683 --> 04:45.986
Sure. I have $3.

04:46.019 --> 04:49.256
Awesome.
Thank you.

04:51.124 --> 04:54.395
Uh, sorry,
actually, um, I forgot.

04:54.428 --> 04:55.629
I -- I kind of need that.

04:55.663 --> 04:56.897
I forgot I have to
pay for parking.

04:56.930 --> 04:59.032
I'm on my way
to Long Beach Memorial.

04:59.066 --> 05:00.801
You gave it to me.
I wasn't thinking.

05:00.834 --> 05:02.736
I -- I need it back.

05:04.538 --> 05:07.074
You really suck.
You know that?

05:07.107 --> 05:09.877
Like, as a person.
Oh, I know.
I know I suck.

05:09.910 --> 05:11.979
But if you could just forget
my suckiness for today,

05:12.012 --> 05:13.481
that would
really help me out.

05:13.514 --> 05:14.848
Ah!

05:14.882 --> 05:16.884
Too late.
Lady bitch.

05:16.917 --> 05:18.686
It's taco time!

05:18.719 --> 05:21.989
Give me the Goddamn money!

05:22.022 --> 05:23.924
Now!
[Man screams]

05:26.560 --> 05:28.462
[Screams]
[Panting]

05:28.496 --> 05:32.199
[Both grunting]

05:32.232 --> 05:33.934
[Sighs]

05:40.307 --> 05:43.043
[Inhales deeply]
Yeah. I'm pretty
much 100% healed.

05:43.076 --> 05:46.246
Does look better.
Shark bite
healed my snake bite.

05:46.279 --> 05:47.648
The constellations, man.

05:47.681 --> 05:49.383
Everything clicks
one by one,

05:49.417 --> 05:52.486
the bird of Hermes descends.
Yeah, it does.

05:52.520 --> 05:56.590
He's also been on heavy
antibiotics for two weeks.

05:56.624 --> 05:57.858
Your sister
picking you up?

05:57.891 --> 05:59.159
Yeah, she'll be here
in a minute.

05:59.192 --> 06:01.228
Thank you!

06:04.364 --> 06:05.766
Everybody's
really looking forward

06:05.799 --> 06:07.000
to getting you back
at the Lodge.

06:07.034 --> 06:08.502
We could use a boost.

06:08.536 --> 06:12.039
It's been kind of a downer
with Scott in charge.

06:12.072 --> 06:15.275
Yeah. I can't believe Jocelyn
let him take Ernie's throne.

06:15.308 --> 06:17.811
Mm-hmm.
Hey,
have you seen Ernie?

06:17.845 --> 06:21.214
No. He asked me to
watch Fernando and his
crow for a few days.

06:21.248 --> 06:23.383
Took a vacation.
Santa Barbara.

06:23.417 --> 06:25.819
He's been slammed at work
since he got back.

06:25.853 --> 06:27.755
Santa Barbara,
that's cool.

06:27.788 --> 06:29.356
That's cool.

06:29.389 --> 06:31.992
He hasn't been around
the Lodge at all.

06:32.025 --> 06:33.260
I think after everything
that happened,

06:33.293 --> 06:35.162
he just needed
some time to himself.

06:35.195 --> 06:37.965
Oh, yeah, that's --
that's cool.

06:37.998 --> 06:40.568
Oh, hey,
I got your supplements.

06:40.601 --> 06:42.202
Oh, great!
Yeah.

06:42.235 --> 06:45.606
Uh, hey, also, tomorrow,
come find me in the library.

06:45.639 --> 06:48.108
Strange doors
are opening, Dud.

06:48.141 --> 06:49.910
I think I found
something important.

06:49.943 --> 06:55.015
Oh, what?
Nothing.
Just the secret fire of life.

06:55.048 --> 06:59.653
**

06:59.687 --> 07:01.455
Gentlemen!

07:01.489 --> 07:04.892
None of us got into
the plumbing game to get famous.

07:04.925 --> 07:07.861
We do what we do,
because we love it.

07:07.895 --> 07:11.198
But some of us are destined
for greater things.

07:11.231 --> 07:14.334
Every month, the Plumbing
Heating Cooling Contractors

07:14.367 --> 07:17.170
of Southern California
puts out its newsletter.

07:17.204 --> 07:21.775
And every month, it sits on
my desk collecting coffee rings.

07:21.809 --> 07:23.911
But not this month.

07:23.944 --> 07:26.814
Because look
who's on the cover.

07:26.847 --> 07:31.218
-Ooh.
-How'd ya pull this off?

07:31.251 --> 07:34.655
I was in Mira Loma
making shit happen at distro.

07:34.688 --> 07:36.990
Wayne from PHCC
was there.

07:37.024 --> 07:39.727
He said, "Could we put you
on the cover next month?"

07:39.760 --> 07:41.829
I said, "Nah, man.
I don't need that noise.

07:41.862 --> 07:43.664
That's not
what I'm about."

07:43.697 --> 07:46.667
But he kept begging me,
so I finally said yes.

07:46.700 --> 07:48.435
Did him a favor.

07:48.468 --> 07:50.437
Well, you did us all
a favor.

07:50.470 --> 07:52.540
It's like
what John Keats said.

07:52.573 --> 07:55.108
"A thing of beauty
is a joy forever."

07:55.142 --> 07:58.779
He was talking about a vase
or a willow tree or something.

07:58.812 --> 08:01.214
But he might as well
have been talking about

08:01.248 --> 08:03.551
West Coast Super Sales.

08:03.584 --> 08:05.285
What's the matter,
Ernie?

08:05.318 --> 08:07.354
Never made the cover
of  The Flow?

08:07.387 --> 08:09.089
What?

08:09.122 --> 08:10.223
Me?

08:10.257 --> 08:12.492
No, no.

08:12.526 --> 08:14.494
Never.

08:16.930 --> 08:18.298
Listen.

08:18.331 --> 08:20.768
I know you've been
getting beat up all over town

08:20.801 --> 08:23.704
cleaning up
after Captain and Orbis.

08:23.737 --> 08:25.038
You want a break?

08:25.072 --> 08:27.741
Maybe hop on
the order desk with Speedy?

08:27.775 --> 08:30.944
Order desk?
No way, I'm a road man.

08:30.978 --> 08:33.781
The road is great
when you're selling.

08:33.814 --> 08:37.551
'04 to '06, those
were golden years, for sure.

08:37.585 --> 08:39.553
But time tells.

08:39.587 --> 08:41.254
I don't know, Bob.

08:41.288 --> 08:45.158
You ever get the feeling
you made a wrong turn?

08:45.192 --> 08:49.830
Like, your life
could be something else?

08:49.863 --> 08:53.000
Jesus, Ernie,
that's gloomy.

08:53.033 --> 08:55.168
I don't like it.

08:55.202 --> 08:58.672
You want to say on the road,
you gotta get your fire back.

08:58.706 --> 09:02.509
Do something
to clear your head.

09:02.542 --> 09:05.946
I signed up
for an online poetry class.

09:05.979 --> 09:09.783
The gal running it has a
master's degree in fine arts.

09:09.817 --> 09:13.253
I am jazzed on language
in a whole new way.

09:13.286 --> 09:15.689
I see poetry everywhere.

09:15.723 --> 09:18.792
The juices are flowing.

09:18.826 --> 09:21.461
Get it?

09:21.494 --> 09:23.530
I get it.

09:23.563 --> 09:26.066
Yeah.
Thanks for the pep talk.

09:26.099 --> 09:27.500
Yeah.

09:27.534 --> 09:29.837
[Telephone ringing
in distance]

09:37.077 --> 09:42.582
**

09:42.616 --> 09:47.955
**

09:47.988 --> 09:50.724
You're awake.

09:52.860 --> 09:54.862
Am I?

09:54.895 --> 09:59.132
We found you sort of, um,
incapacitated at the tavern.

09:59.166 --> 10:01.534
Too much whiskey,
perhaps.

10:01.568 --> 10:03.303
Wasn't the whiskey.

10:03.336 --> 10:07.107
What was it?

10:07.140 --> 10:09.810
Is this Lodge 1?

10:09.843 --> 10:12.312
Do you remember
us helping you up here?

10:12.345 --> 10:15.849
I don't remember anything.
I never do.

10:15.883 --> 10:18.719
I have...

10:18.752 --> 10:22.089
the feeling
of having a memory,

10:22.122 --> 10:26.593
just not the actual memory.

10:29.429 --> 10:32.733
My tongue
feels like sandpaper.

10:32.766 --> 10:34.634
Have some water.

10:36.636 --> 10:38.171
Connie, um...

10:38.205 --> 10:41.641
we have all enjoyed having you
the last couple of weeks.

10:41.675 --> 10:44.745
But still, some of us
have been a little worried

10:44.778 --> 10:47.781
that here in London,
you might, um...

10:47.815 --> 10:53.620
**

10:53.653 --> 10:55.122
There's a glass
right there.

10:55.155 --> 10:58.558
**

10:58.591 --> 11:01.962
Hey, have you talked
to anyone about the bill?

11:01.995 --> 11:03.831
Well, yeah.
Admin guy.

11:03.864 --> 11:05.598
Yeah, he said there's
stuff I can do, you know.

11:05.632 --> 11:08.101
Funds from the state
and, I don't know,

11:08.135 --> 11:10.270
all I gotta do
is the paperwork.

11:10.303 --> 11:12.672
Liz? Come on, relax.

11:12.706 --> 11:15.108
What are they gonna do,
I mean, like repo my stitches?

11:15.142 --> 11:17.677
Your follow-ups,
your medication.

11:17.711 --> 11:19.880
Yeah, no,
Blaise has got me covered.

11:19.913 --> 11:21.214
He's hooking me up, yeah.

11:21.248 --> 11:23.751
Getting better
way ahead of schedule.

11:23.784 --> 11:25.786
All I gotta do is convalesce on
the couch for a little while,

11:25.819 --> 11:27.587
then I'm moving into
the trailer full-time,

11:27.620 --> 11:29.356
out of your hair,
I promise, right?

11:29.389 --> 11:31.158
Hey? Hey,
you want to hit up Donuts?

11:31.191 --> 11:34.795
Sure,
but before we do...

11:34.828 --> 11:37.564
there's something
you should know.

11:40.768 --> 11:42.269
It's a family.

11:42.302 --> 11:44.772
They start moving in
last week.

11:50.210 --> 11:52.345
Mmm.

11:52.379 --> 11:55.682
This is...

11:55.715 --> 11:57.084
great.

11:57.117 --> 11:59.286
[Laughs]
This is great.

11:59.319 --> 12:01.855
Yeah, this is great.

12:01.889 --> 12:04.057
It's a family biz.

12:04.091 --> 12:06.093
Keeping it a pool shop.

12:06.126 --> 12:07.761
Come on.

12:07.795 --> 12:09.129
I love it.

12:09.162 --> 12:11.331
[Laughs]
Love it.

12:11.364 --> 12:14.701
Good luck, Pool Party.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.503
Love it.

12:18.305 --> 12:22.175
So, that's the final word.
No Grand Tour.

12:22.209 --> 12:26.546
London's phasing it out.
It's, uh -- it's too expensive.

12:26.579 --> 12:29.783
Although, there is, um,
a CD-ROM you can send away for.

12:29.817 --> 12:32.452
It's a kind of
virtual interactive tour

12:32.485 --> 12:34.254
of various Lodges
around the globe.

12:34.287 --> 12:36.824
Nope. [Exhales sharply]
Nope. That's fine.

12:36.857 --> 12:38.225
No, I understand.

12:38.258 --> 12:40.227
It's the smart thing to do.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.195
People have to learn.

12:42.229 --> 12:44.697
I just want everyone
to understand

12:44.731 --> 12:46.934
that I have London's
full blessing.

12:46.967 --> 12:49.502
I feel there's been
a little confusion around here

12:49.536 --> 12:51.404
as to who's in charge.

12:51.438 --> 12:54.107
Um, how do you mean?

12:54.141 --> 13:00.247
Well, I -- some people might
think that because you're here,

13:00.280 --> 13:03.951
from London, you have
more authority than me.

13:03.984 --> 13:05.318
Oh, don't worry, Scott.

13:05.352 --> 13:07.720
You're definitely
in charge of Lodge 49.

13:07.754 --> 13:10.757
[Sighs]
Although, obviously,

13:10.790 --> 13:12.792
as the Lodge is
technically under probation,

13:12.826 --> 13:15.028
I will need to sign off
on any proposals

13:15.062 --> 13:16.763
you might have
going forward.

13:21.401 --> 13:25.005
Gerson, this is just
a standard performance review.

13:25.038 --> 13:27.207
You didn't have to
wear a suit.

13:27.240 --> 13:30.243
Exactly.

13:30.277 --> 13:33.180
Okay.

13:33.213 --> 13:36.716
Uh, "speaking on behalf of
the entire executive carousel

13:36.749 --> 13:39.552
at Omni Capital Partners
Food Service West,

13:39.586 --> 13:42.389
your work here
in greatly appreciated."

13:42.422 --> 13:44.724
Thanks.
[Clears throat]

13:44.757 --> 13:46.826
"But due to the...

13:46.860 --> 13:50.463
capricious nature
of global markets,

13:50.497 --> 13:54.601
it is impossible at this time
to authorize the..."

13:57.737 --> 14:00.807
Listen.
There aren't any raises.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.309
I tried.

14:02.342 --> 14:04.477
I really tried.
Rat!

14:04.511 --> 14:07.047
No, hey, come on.
No, no, there's a rat!

14:07.080 --> 14:08.681
[Rat squeaking]

14:08.715 --> 14:12.819
Ooh! Ooh, shit! Oh! Um...
[Women screaming]

14:12.852 --> 14:15.422
[Clattering in distance]

14:18.091 --> 14:20.994
The rat
is the king of history.

14:21.028 --> 14:23.196
He always wins.

14:32.139 --> 14:34.407
Well, this sucks.

14:34.441 --> 14:36.944
Liz:
I needed grocery money.

14:36.977 --> 14:39.947
Burt gave me $75.

14:43.550 --> 14:46.353
Hey? You've got
roof access, right?

14:46.386 --> 14:48.455
So, you know,
you don't have a TV,

14:48.488 --> 14:51.424
go up
and look at the stars.

14:51.458 --> 14:54.061
You can't see stars
in Long Beach.

14:54.094 --> 14:56.229
Uh-huh.

14:59.532 --> 15:01.434
You know, I could
hook you up at Temp Joy.

15:01.468 --> 15:05.905
Ross said if I bring
a new client, I get 50 bucks.

15:05.939 --> 15:07.107
Split that with you.

15:07.140 --> 15:08.308
Sweet. [Sighs]

15:08.341 --> 15:10.443
My connections
are paying off.

15:10.477 --> 15:11.878
God, come on, look.

15:11.911 --> 15:14.114
I know things look
a little shaky right now,

15:14.147 --> 15:15.815
but you're in
a great spot.

15:15.848 --> 15:16.950
We both are.

15:16.984 --> 15:18.585
Liz,
you paid off your debt.

15:18.618 --> 15:21.354
Everybody dreams about
doing that and you did it.

15:21.388 --> 15:22.855
[Laughs] Yeah.

15:22.889 --> 15:25.658
And my foot...

15:25.692 --> 15:28.695
it's healed.

15:28.728 --> 15:29.896
Don't you see?

15:29.929 --> 15:33.433
Liz, we made it through
the worst year ever.

15:33.466 --> 15:36.903
And now we're free,
we are in open water.

15:36.936 --> 15:39.006
Dud, you almost died.

15:39.039 --> 15:40.007
Again.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.175
[Laughs] I know.

15:42.209 --> 15:44.411
I know.

15:44.444 --> 15:47.814
But it was different
this time.

15:47.847 --> 15:49.949
I saw something.

15:49.983 --> 15:51.684
What?

15:52.919 --> 15:54.287
I saw...

15:54.321 --> 15:57.057
light.

15:57.090 --> 16:03.263
I -- I can't explain it really,
but I just, the...

16:03.296 --> 16:05.432
The shark was a gift.

16:05.465 --> 16:07.500
And it changed me.

16:09.569 --> 16:13.106
And...

16:13.140 --> 16:16.743
it's like
I got a message from Dad.

16:18.511 --> 16:22.582
The universe is good
and I'm on the right path.

16:22.615 --> 16:24.784
What are you talking
about?

16:30.090 --> 16:33.560
Dud, that day on the beach,
I thought I'd lost you.

16:35.728 --> 16:38.798
And if I lost you,
I'd have no one.

16:40.300 --> 16:41.968
[Clears throat]

16:44.104 --> 16:47.240
I am all alone.

16:47.274 --> 16:50.710
Wait,
you're not alone.

16:50.743 --> 16:52.412
I'm always here.

16:57.650 --> 16:59.419
Look...

17:03.390 --> 17:05.925
I think you should come
to the Lodge.

17:08.495 --> 17:13.866
I know, I --
but I found a mentor there.

17:13.900 --> 17:15.868
You know, someone
that's there for me

17:15.902 --> 17:18.905
and someone that...

17:18.938 --> 17:21.941
cares about me.

17:21.974 --> 17:26.879
**

17:26.913 --> 17:29.149
[Crow squawking]

17:29.182 --> 17:32.185
**

17:37.890 --> 17:40.893
**

17:46.599 --> 17:49.602
**

17:55.108 --> 17:58.445
[Crow squawking]

18:09.856 --> 18:11.624
[Whispers] Liz?

18:11.658 --> 18:14.494
Liz, hey?
Hey, are you -- are you awake?

18:16.763 --> 18:18.298
Liz?

18:20.833 --> 18:23.470
What do you want?

18:23.503 --> 18:26.873
I wanted to tell you something.
I couldn't wait, sorry.

18:33.813 --> 18:35.715
Liz...

18:35.748 --> 18:38.718
I'm proud of you.

18:38.751 --> 18:40.453
For what?

18:40.487 --> 18:43.156
I don't --
I don't know.

18:43.190 --> 18:45.358
I just am.

18:45.392 --> 18:48.895
I've done nothing
with my life.

18:48.928 --> 18:50.730
So what?

18:50.763 --> 18:55.668
You have so many great things
inside of you.

18:57.270 --> 18:58.571
Dad used to say that
a lot.

18:58.605 --> 18:59.939
It actually
kind of scared him

18:59.972 --> 19:02.475
and he didn't know
what to do with all that...

19:02.509 --> 19:06.979
great stuff inside you.

19:10.650 --> 19:13.920
Dad didn't understand me
sometimes.

19:13.953 --> 19:16.423
But he loved you.

19:16.456 --> 19:18.358
Mmm.

19:38.578 --> 19:40.413
Night.

19:44.717 --> 19:46.319
[Door thuds]

19:49.356 --> 19:52.725
**

19:52.759 --> 19:56.195
Something is missing.
I just don't know what.

19:58.130 --> 20:00.032
No, as -- as kids,

20:00.066 --> 20:02.369
me and my brother
would play Chutes and Ladders

20:02.402 --> 20:04.671
and for some reason,
I always thought it was more fun

20:04.704 --> 20:06.873
going down the chute
than climbing the ladder,

20:06.906 --> 20:09.442
even if that meant losing,
so...

20:09.476 --> 20:12.445
That was screwed up,
obviously.

20:13.746 --> 20:16.249
But when I paid off my debt
and got to zero,

20:16.283 --> 20:19.752
I thought I'd be like,
"I'm a zero!"

20:19.786 --> 20:23.122
But instead, it's like,
"I'm a zero."

20:23.155 --> 20:24.156
You know what I mean?

20:24.190 --> 20:25.658
Zero?

20:25.692 --> 20:28.295
Nothing in my life
adds up.

20:28.328 --> 20:30.263
Where have I been?
Nowhere.

20:30.297 --> 20:32.565
What have I been doing?
Nothing.

20:32.599 --> 20:36.469
Like, restaurants, retail,
six months as a paralegal.

20:36.503 --> 20:40.407
I mean, I told people
I was a paralegal,

20:40.440 --> 20:45.244
but I was really like, just an
office assistant, you know?

20:45.278 --> 20:47.347
Files, getting coffee.

20:47.380 --> 20:50.182
The lawyer was the sister
of this idiot I dated

20:50.216 --> 20:52.752
for like three seconds
in San Diego.

20:52.785 --> 20:54.954
Bobby. Ugh.

20:54.987 --> 20:56.889
[Laughs]

20:56.923 --> 21:00.159
And that was my best job!

21:00.192 --> 21:03.963
It's all just a zigzag
to nowhere, I mean...

21:03.996 --> 21:06.433
Yesterday, I assaulted
a homeless guy in the park.

21:06.466 --> 21:10.370
What?
So, you -- you ask me
what I'm looking for?

21:10.403 --> 21:12.405
I don't have a clue,
Ross.

21:12.439 --> 21:16.743
I'm just like, sliding
down through the cracks.

21:16.776 --> 21:19.979
I'm sorry. I had like, three
coffees before I got here.

21:20.012 --> 21:22.649
[Laughs] I know hearing
about my crap isn't your job.

21:22.682 --> 21:26.085
No, it...
kind of is.

21:26.118 --> 21:27.554
I'm here to help.

21:27.587 --> 21:29.356
I mean,
I can't really speak

21:29.389 --> 21:31.458
to some of
these deeper things,

21:31.491 --> 21:34.126
but you should know
that from what I've seen,

21:34.160 --> 21:35.395
your feelings
are in line

21:35.428 --> 21:38.498
with a large portion
of the workforce.

21:38.531 --> 21:39.999
You're right.
Yeah.

21:40.032 --> 21:42.702
I don't know why I'm being such
a crybaby today. [Laughs]

21:42.735 --> 21:44.737
Listen.
Your test scores are good.

21:44.771 --> 21:46.839
You've got a great
recommendation
from your brother,

21:46.873 --> 21:48.741
who's one of our best.

21:48.775 --> 21:51.043
And to be honest,
you're not the first person

21:51.077 --> 21:53.680
to come through Temp Joy
with some past legal issues.

21:53.713 --> 21:56.683
So, yeah,
we'll get you in the mix.

21:56.716 --> 21:59.752
Great. Thanks.

21:59.786 --> 22:01.020
Liz!

22:01.053 --> 22:03.756
Rats?
Champ has a fever.

22:03.790 --> 22:05.458
He's hoping
it's bubonic plague

22:05.492 --> 22:07.360
and says he wants
to take that ride.

22:07.394 --> 22:08.595
[Both chuckle]

22:08.628 --> 22:10.262
Wait, so,
Shamroxx is like, gone?

22:10.296 --> 22:12.198
Yeah,
the building's condemned.

22:12.231 --> 22:13.766
We got our notices
immediately.

22:13.800 --> 22:17.470
Janet sent out a memo
saying it was all net positive.

22:17.504 --> 22:21.307
She said something new was
about to rise from the ashes.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.543
Blammo.

22:23.576 --> 22:25.244
I need to
find something fast.

22:25.277 --> 22:26.579
Sarah's not working
right now.

22:26.613 --> 22:28.615
Something will come up.

22:30.249 --> 22:32.018
It's great to see you,
Liz.

22:32.051 --> 22:34.353
I think we've done a good job
repairing our relationship

22:34.387 --> 22:36.022
since the affair.

22:36.055 --> 22:37.356
We didn't have an affair.

22:37.390 --> 22:38.725
Well, we made-out.

22:38.758 --> 22:39.859
No, we didn't.

22:39.892 --> 22:42.829
We kissed.
Not really.

22:42.862 --> 22:45.465
Our lips did touch.

22:45.498 --> 22:50.069
I mean, you have to
face that fact, Liz.

22:50.102 --> 22:53.673
Okay.
Technically, fine.

22:53.706 --> 22:57.009
Oh. [Laughs]

22:57.043 --> 22:59.579
Well, if I hear Omni's got
any stuff going on,

22:59.612 --> 23:01.180
you know, I'll --
I'll let you know.

23:01.213 --> 23:02.782
No. Thanks.

23:02.815 --> 23:05.885
Uh, I'll take my chances
elsewhere.

23:05.918 --> 23:07.587
Mmm.

23:09.622 --> 23:11.424
Yes.

23:14.193 --> 23:16.629
Oh.

23:16.663 --> 23:18.364
Good luck.

23:22.702 --> 23:25.738
Holy shit,
what is that?

23:25.772 --> 23:28.508
No one else knows
about this.

23:28.541 --> 23:30.810
I want to keep it
that way.

23:32.178 --> 23:33.980
So, you're gonna do it!

23:34.013 --> 23:35.982
You're gonna complete
the magnum opus, just
like Wallace Smith!

23:36.015 --> 23:38.685
Yeah. Well, actually,
I don't know that he did.

23:38.718 --> 23:42.288
Uh, his final act baffles me,
but I'm been preparing,

23:42.321 --> 23:44.356
collecting instruments
and ingredients

23:44.390 --> 23:45.725
for the material process,

23:45.758 --> 23:48.060
which mirrors
the spiritual process.

23:48.094 --> 23:50.162
Making gold.
In a way.

23:50.196 --> 23:52.999
No, I get it. It's an
allegorical metaphor, but still.

23:53.032 --> 23:56.569
First, I -- I need to crack
the code on the diary.

23:56.603 --> 23:57.970
Yeah, yeah.
Yeah, right.

23:58.004 --> 23:59.405
But, uh, don't you think
that we should go,

23:59.438 --> 24:00.973
you know,
find El Confidente?

24:01.007 --> 24:03.209
You know, get some info
on the scrolls?

24:03.242 --> 24:05.244
We don't even know
if El Confidente exists.

24:05.277 --> 24:08.548
He might just be a figment
of Larry's imagination.
Yeah. Right.

24:08.581 --> 24:11.618
I mean, El Confidente's
probably just another metaphor.

24:11.651 --> 24:12.885
Shadows and riddles,
right?

24:12.919 --> 24:14.420
Exactly.
Yeah.

24:14.453 --> 24:16.656
The diary is the thing,

24:16.689 --> 24:19.225
so I've been collecting all
the books written by Merrill,

24:19.258 --> 24:22.028
trying to find a clue,
but...

24:22.061 --> 24:25.898
it's a lot, yeah.

24:25.932 --> 24:30.670
Which is why, Dud...

24:30.703 --> 24:35.374
I was hoping that
you would be my...

24:35.407 --> 24:37.777
apprentice.

24:37.810 --> 24:39.211
Are you serious?!

24:39.245 --> 24:41.313
Yeah.
Yes!

24:41.347 --> 24:44.551
Of course!

24:44.584 --> 24:46.586
Great.
Uh, yeah, but why me?

24:46.619 --> 24:48.487
Because I'm way behind
on all this stuff.

24:48.521 --> 24:50.557
Seen and unseen, man.

24:50.590 --> 24:53.025
You know
what I'm talking about.

24:53.059 --> 24:55.728
You got a glimpse of it
on the beach in the light.

24:55.762 --> 24:59.766
Seeing your dad,
the Tongva.

24:59.799 --> 25:02.501
The star field at Orbis.

25:02.535 --> 25:03.703
Did I tell you all that?

25:03.736 --> 25:07.774
In the hospital.
The painkillers.

25:07.807 --> 25:09.542
Yeah, I mean, I...

25:09.576 --> 25:12.044
I guess it could just be
all the toxic fumes in Orbis.

25:12.078 --> 25:14.080
Could've been all that blood
that I lost on the beach.

25:14.113 --> 25:16.549
No. Don't do that.

25:18.685 --> 25:19.952
Yeah.

25:19.986 --> 25:22.188
I don't think so, either.

25:24.891 --> 25:26.893
Thanks, Blaise.

25:26.926 --> 25:29.295
God, but what do I do
with all that?

25:29.328 --> 25:30.863
So, Merrill
was a polymath.

25:30.897 --> 25:31.964
He wrote books on

25:31.998 --> 25:35.101
alchemy, economics,
geology, architecture.

25:35.134 --> 25:37.536
Nobody reads 'em anymore,
because his ideas are obsolete.

25:37.570 --> 25:41.608
Mm-hmm.
The Hollow Earth theory
didn't really pan out.

25:41.641 --> 25:43.009
But you can't take him
literally.

25:43.042 --> 25:45.778
He loved maps, so he wrote
a book on cartography.

25:45.812 --> 25:46.913
He had this idea that

25:46.946 --> 25:49.816
everyone navigates the world
using two maps,

25:49.849 --> 25:52.585
a physical map,
cities and the streets,

25:52.619 --> 25:56.088
but underneath it,
there's a mystical map...

25:56.122 --> 25:58.190
Huh.
...that shows the spots

25:58.224 --> 26:02.228
where the world seems to
let us in on a secret.

26:02.261 --> 26:03.596
[Laughs]

26:03.630 --> 26:07.133
Most people navigate
using just the physical map,

26:07.166 --> 26:10.870
but alchemists
move between the two.

26:10.903 --> 26:14.006
The daylight world,
going to work, eating burritos,

26:14.040 --> 26:18.745
but then there's that other map
waiting down below.

26:21.180 --> 26:23.382
Oh.

26:23.415 --> 26:26.653
This is crazy.
This is crazy. [Chuckles]

26:26.686 --> 26:28.688
Man, I just feel like
everything in my life's

26:28.721 --> 26:31.023
finally
starting to add up.

26:31.057 --> 26:32.491
Lightning in a bottle.

26:32.524 --> 26:34.093
Lightning in a bottle.

26:34.126 --> 26:36.595
Just...

26:36.629 --> 26:37.830
[Sighs]

26:37.864 --> 26:39.632
Feel free.

26:39.666 --> 26:43.703
I feel free to do
whatever I want.

26:43.736 --> 26:47.306
What would you do
if you could do anything?

26:47.339 --> 26:49.308
That's easy.

26:49.341 --> 26:51.277
Clean pools.

26:51.310 --> 26:55.114
**

26:55.147 --> 26:56.548
You know, Alice,

26:56.582 --> 26:58.751
I really want to get you
something nice

26:58.785 --> 27:00.619
for saving my life.

27:00.653 --> 27:02.855
I told you,
I don't want anything.

27:02.889 --> 27:04.390
I know, I know.

27:04.423 --> 27:06.158
But, you know, it's just,
I can't help but feel

27:06.192 --> 27:09.195
it's not fair that I'm the one
getting celebrated in the paper

27:09.228 --> 27:11.898
and you're not.
No one's celebrating you.

27:11.931 --> 27:13.966
Ehh...

27:14.000 --> 27:15.467
Yeah.

27:15.501 --> 27:18.104
What about a new board?

27:18.137 --> 27:19.638
Or like...

27:21.273 --> 27:24.643
...state-of-the-art
electronics?

27:24.677 --> 27:26.879
[Laughs]
You don't have any money, dude.

27:26.913 --> 27:29.615
Mmm.

27:29.648 --> 27:32.551
[Door dings]

27:32.584 --> 27:34.053
Sean Dudley?

27:34.086 --> 27:36.522
Yeah?

27:36.555 --> 27:38.657
I'm here
to give you money.

27:38.691 --> 27:42.261
**

27:44.797 --> 27:48.167
Dud:
So...you're a lawyer.

27:48.200 --> 27:50.102
Call me whatever you want.

27:50.136 --> 27:52.071
I read about you in the paper,
you were in pain.

27:52.104 --> 27:54.440
I'm here to fix that.
Oh, my leg?

27:54.473 --> 27:55.908
No, I mean,
it hurts a little bit,

27:55.942 --> 27:57.910
but it's healing okay and
it's gonna have a crazy scar.

27:57.944 --> 28:00.279
You suffered a tragedy.
You deserve to be compensated.

28:00.312 --> 28:01.680
The responsible party
has to pay.

28:01.714 --> 28:04.483
Well, I don't -- I don't think
you can sue the ocean.

28:04.516 --> 28:06.018
State, county, city.

28:06.052 --> 28:07.653
What if I told you they all
knew about the shark problem

28:07.686 --> 28:09.889
and they covered it up,
those greedy bastards?

28:09.922 --> 28:11.690
Shit.

28:11.724 --> 28:14.827
Really?
Oh, yeah.
That could definitely be true.

28:14.861 --> 28:16.662
Okay, look, now that
we're working together,

28:16.695 --> 28:18.998
you only have one job
and that is to trust me.
Yeah.

28:19.031 --> 28:19.999
Got it?
Mm-hmm.

28:20.032 --> 28:21.433
They don't want
to go to trial.

28:21.467 --> 28:22.835
They're gonna want
to settle fast,

28:22.869 --> 28:24.837
so I will provide
my law services pro bono,

28:24.871 --> 28:26.839
which is Latin
for "free" --
I know what pro bono means.

28:26.873 --> 28:28.507
-- until we get
your medical expenses paid,

28:28.540 --> 28:30.209
plus, a nice, fat chunk
on top of that, okay?

28:30.242 --> 28:33.512
Now, I'll just need you
for the occasional deposition.

28:33.545 --> 28:36.015
I like to go deep,
get a lot of detail.

28:36.048 --> 28:39.018
Other than that, you just sit
back and wait for the money.

28:39.051 --> 28:40.686
It's guaranteed.

28:40.719 --> 28:41.687
So...

28:41.720 --> 28:43.790
this is pretty much
guaranteed?

28:43.823 --> 28:45.624
So, this is pretty much
guaranteed.

28:45.657 --> 28:46.959
And what I want to do,
Burt,

28:46.993 --> 28:48.494
is leverage some
of my future shark earnings.

28:48.527 --> 28:51.297
Okay, let's say, mmm,
a grand, for now,

28:51.330 --> 28:54.500
okay, on friendly terms,
okay?

28:54.533 --> 28:56.402
And then down the road,
I'll give you, like,

28:56.435 --> 28:58.637
10% of my settlement.

29:03.309 --> 29:05.878
Where did you go
to law school?

29:05.912 --> 29:07.379
Yale.

29:07.413 --> 29:09.181
Yale, Burt.

29:09.215 --> 29:10.649
Yale.

29:12.151 --> 29:13.652
Okay.

29:13.685 --> 29:16.923
30% on the grand,
month term,

29:16.956 --> 29:22.461
plus, I get a dime on whatever
your law provider brings in.

29:22.494 --> 29:23.930
I'll write it up.

29:23.963 --> 29:26.598
Great and, uh, I'm gonna
grab Liz's TV while I'm here,

29:26.632 --> 29:28.000
because we need that.

29:28.034 --> 29:31.403
Uh, and I'll take
one of these, too.

29:33.105 --> 29:34.673
Right.

29:34.706 --> 29:37.176
You're like an angel.
Mmm. Yeah, yeah.

29:37.209 --> 29:38.710
I am.

29:39.979 --> 29:43.983
Ooh!
That looks like
a Goddamn dragon bite.

29:44.016 --> 29:47.419
[Laughs] Dragon of the sea,
man, yeah.

29:47.453 --> 29:48.754
[Bell ringing in distance]
Uh, is Ernie here,

29:48.787 --> 29:49.922
'cause I can't wait to
tell him the whole story.

29:49.956 --> 29:52.158
Didn't he come
to the hospital?

29:53.359 --> 29:57.029
Nah.
Are you sure you can drink,
taking antibiotics?

29:57.063 --> 30:00.833
Yeah. Mmm. I think that's
just something doctors say.

30:00.867 --> 30:01.868
People?!

30:01.901 --> 30:04.803
I've been ringing the bell,
let's go!

30:04.837 --> 30:06.505
Come on,
you knights and knaves,

30:06.538 --> 30:08.074
let's start the meeting.

30:10.709 --> 30:14.480
Maybe we should...
wait for Ernie?

30:16.115 --> 30:17.783
So, mark your calendars.

30:17.816 --> 30:21.020
We have Mystic Chords of Memory
coming up.

30:21.053 --> 30:22.754
Plus, the rummage sale

30:22.788 --> 30:26.392
and the official start
of bowling season.

30:26.425 --> 30:29.962
[Clears throat]
Uh, finally...

30:31.330 --> 30:34.433
...as you know, London
has put us under probation.

30:34.466 --> 30:37.669
Which means it is incumbent
upon all of us

30:37.703 --> 30:41.407
to come together and meet
their stipulated benchmarks,

30:41.440 --> 30:43.142
in terms of boosting
membership numbers

30:43.175 --> 30:47.113
and maintaining
our financial responsibilities.

30:47.146 --> 30:48.480
Now, I'm going to be placing

30:48.514 --> 30:50.482
more ads
about renting out the hall.

30:50.516 --> 30:53.685
Weddings, funerals, seminars,
whatever.

30:53.719 --> 30:56.022
We cannot have this place
sitting here empty

30:56.055 --> 30:57.289
on the weekends.

30:57.323 --> 31:01.360
So, that means more volunteers
to oversee events.

31:09.235 --> 31:11.938
Also, I am calling in
everyone's bar tabs.

31:11.971 --> 31:14.173
[Indistinct yelling]
What?! No!

31:14.206 --> 31:16.108
Scott, this is nuts!

31:16.142 --> 31:19.645
Austerity doesn't work!
Exactly.
It's a Puritan wet dream.

31:19.678 --> 31:22.714
Yeah,
total wet dream.
Jocelyn, man,
did you approve this?

31:22.748 --> 31:24.516
Uh, well, Scott and I went
through the books together.

31:24.550 --> 31:26.485
Whoa, whoa, wait, wait,
wait a minute.

31:26.518 --> 31:28.320
I  approved it. Okay?

31:28.354 --> 31:30.756
Me.
Sovereign Protector, all right?

31:30.789 --> 31:34.293
That's all that matters.
[Indistinct muttering]

31:34.326 --> 31:37.796
Oh, come on? Larry let
this place fall to pieces!

31:37.829 --> 31:41.533
Now, we have to face reality,
okay?

31:41.567 --> 31:45.037
Oh, nice!
Nice attitude, Rooney.

31:47.273 --> 31:50.276
**

31:55.147 --> 31:56.848
[Laughs]

32:01.453 --> 32:05.657
Careful.
That is an Orbiscope.

32:05.691 --> 32:07.426
Merrill designed it
himself.

32:07.459 --> 32:09.028
Sorry.

32:09.061 --> 32:10.362
Oh, you're fine.

32:10.396 --> 32:12.531
I didn't mean to sneak up
on you.

32:12.564 --> 32:15.067
I'm Clara.

32:15.101 --> 32:19.171
Don't remember the last time I
saw someone else in the archive.

32:19.205 --> 32:23.142
You looking
for something?

32:23.175 --> 32:24.776
My mind.

32:24.810 --> 32:27.446
[Laughs]
Uh, I don't know.

32:27.479 --> 32:30.216
I saw an old engraving
in the tavern.

32:30.249 --> 32:31.917
It wasn't marked, but...

32:31.950 --> 32:36.855
I swear it looked like the view
from Signal Hill in Long Beach.

32:36.888 --> 32:39.025
Wait, Lodge 49?

32:39.058 --> 32:40.359
You're Connie, yes?

32:40.392 --> 32:41.994
Yeah. [Laughs]

32:42.028 --> 32:44.230
I've heard about your exploits
in the tavern.

32:44.263 --> 32:46.265
Thank you.

32:46.298 --> 32:49.001
[Laughs]
I grew up in Long Beach.

32:49.035 --> 32:53.972
I'm trying to write something
about it, but I can't.

32:54.006 --> 32:55.374
Writer's block?

32:55.407 --> 32:57.576
Yeah.

32:57.609 --> 32:59.445
You're on a deadline?

32:59.478 --> 33:01.580
Oh, yeah.

33:05.184 --> 33:08.554
I swear to God...

33:08.587 --> 33:13.059
my mind is melting.

33:13.092 --> 33:15.061
Melting?

33:16.662 --> 33:19.565
Do you ever see things
that aren't there?

33:22.134 --> 33:24.836
Oh, my God.
[Laughs]

33:24.870 --> 33:26.305
Listen to me!

33:26.338 --> 33:27.839
If you wouldn't mind,

33:27.873 --> 33:31.777
I'd like you
to talk to my boss, Melinda.

33:31.810 --> 33:34.246
Melinda?

33:34.280 --> 33:36.848
I think
she could help you.

33:36.882 --> 33:42.521
**

33:42.554 --> 33:48.360
1...2...3...4...

33:48.394 --> 33:51.430
Nocturia.

33:51.463 --> 33:53.199
There's pills
I can take.

33:53.232 --> 33:55.000
That's good.

33:55.033 --> 33:57.436
Alice's mom keeps yelling at me
to get checked.

33:57.469 --> 33:59.037
[Door dings]

34:01.473 --> 34:05.811
Hi. Uh, Paul, right?
I'm Greg.

34:05.844 --> 34:07.446
This is my beautiful wife,
Greta,

34:07.479 --> 34:08.780
and this is our son,
Booie.

34:08.814 --> 34:10.249
We're your new neighbors.

34:10.282 --> 34:12.251
Welcome.

34:12.284 --> 34:13.585
Aloha.

34:16.388 --> 34:18.524
Well, just wanted
to come by and say hey.

34:18.557 --> 34:20.926
Uh, also,
we need to talk about parking.

34:20.959 --> 34:22.261
Uh, I don't want
any of your customers

34:22.294 --> 34:23.529
in front of Pool Party.

34:23.562 --> 34:26.064
Booie needs two spaces
to park his truck.

34:26.098 --> 34:28.267
Cool?

34:28.300 --> 34:29.535
Great.

34:29.568 --> 34:32.271
Also, I've noticed
some graffiti around.

34:32.304 --> 34:33.572
Street gangs.

34:33.605 --> 34:35.774
I think that we could all
keep an eye on that.

34:35.807 --> 34:39.511
Well, Booie,
do you want a latte?

34:39.545 --> 34:40.946
One latte for Booie.

34:40.979 --> 34:43.014
You want some whipped cream
on that, Booie?

34:43.048 --> 34:45.517
Uh...we don't have latte.

34:48.120 --> 34:49.421
[Door dings]

34:49.455 --> 34:52.558
Booie?!
Honey, it's okay!

34:52.591 --> 34:55.026
We can go to
a real coffee shop!

34:57.062 --> 34:59.431
They won't last.

35:04.236 --> 35:05.137
[  Beep  ]

35:05.171 --> 35:06.972
Ernie?
I'm at Harbor Municipal.

35:07.005 --> 35:08.340
Where are you, man?

35:08.374 --> 35:11.643
This is like total flakeage.

35:11.677 --> 35:13.745
Uh...
No, seriously,

35:13.779 --> 35:15.747
no -- no worries,
no worries, no, you know,

35:15.781 --> 35:18.016
I just thought
I might catch you here

35:18.049 --> 35:21.353
since I didn't really see you
at the hospital

35:21.387 --> 35:22.954
and you're not
returning calls.

35:22.988 --> 35:26.258
Um, I'm -- I'm sure you're
just slammed at work,

35:26.292 --> 35:28.760
so can't wait to hear about
your -- all about your vacay

35:28.794 --> 35:31.530
to Santa Barbara.
[Laughs]

35:31.563 --> 35:33.665
Uh...so elegant there,
isn't it?

35:33.699 --> 35:38.304
I mean, the, uh,
wine and the artichoke dip.

35:38.337 --> 35:41.573
I mean, I've never really
been there, but, um, still...

35:41.607 --> 35:43.642
Anyway, uh...

35:43.675 --> 35:45.544
Yeah, nothing new with me.

35:45.577 --> 35:47.679
You know, besides,
uh, shark attack

35:47.713 --> 35:51.217
and, uh, I'm feeling great,
healing fast.

35:51.250 --> 35:52.851
So, yeah...

35:52.884 --> 35:55.421
Uh, looking forward
to catching up, man.

35:55.454 --> 35:57.523
[Laughs]

36:00.659 --> 36:03.395
Metz:  Stone felt at home
among the Fjords.

36:03.429 --> 36:07.266
The cold water, the jagged
rocks, the purifying wind.

36:07.299 --> 36:10.802
Yes, this was just what he
needed after the unholy events

36:10.836 --> 36:13.705
that took place hours earlier
on the Slottsplassen.

36:13.739 --> 36:17.776
18 people dead, some of them
friends, some of them lovers.
[Donkey braying]

36:17.809 --> 36:21.079
All of them burnt to a crisp
by a flamethrower.

36:21.112 --> 36:26.418
**

36:50.742 --> 36:52.210
Ooh. Hi. [Chuckles]
Oh, hi.

36:52.244 --> 36:55.547
Um, do you know if there's
a Dr. Kimbrough in there?

36:55.581 --> 36:57.283
Uh, no, he's over there.

36:57.316 --> 36:58.450
We share a waiting room.

36:58.484 --> 37:01.420
Oh. Thanks.
I'm temping for him.

37:01.453 --> 37:03.889
Oh. Uh, well...

37:03.922 --> 37:06.958
good luck
with "Doctor" Kimbrough.

37:17.603 --> 37:18.737
[Door opens]

37:18.770 --> 37:21.340
Man: Shut up
and eat your pudding!

37:21.373 --> 37:22.941
No, you are
the pudding toad!

37:22.974 --> 37:25.411
I'm hanging up.
I'm hanging up.

37:25.444 --> 37:28.079
[Telephone rings]

37:31.350 --> 37:33.018
Who are you?

37:33.051 --> 37:34.620
Uh, Liz Dudley.

37:34.653 --> 37:36.388
Temp Joy sent me.

37:36.422 --> 37:37.756
Are you Dr. Kimbrough?

37:37.789 --> 37:40.959
Yes, I'm Dr. Kimbrough.
God, Jesus!

37:40.992 --> 37:42.260
Who else would I be?

37:42.294 --> 37:45.230
No, I just thought this was
going to be a doctor's office.

37:45.263 --> 37:48.166
I have a PhD
in accounting.

37:48.199 --> 37:50.001
[Telephone rings]

37:50.035 --> 37:52.638
Okay, why don't you
answer the phone?

37:52.671 --> 37:54.440
It's your job.

37:56.942 --> 37:59.144
Hi, you've reached
Dr. Kimbrough's off--

38:00.979 --> 38:02.548
[Whispers]
What? Who is it?

38:02.581 --> 38:04.115
Who is it?!

38:04.149 --> 38:06.518
Uh, a woman.

38:06.552 --> 38:10.021
She said she wants the toad
to call her back.

38:10.055 --> 38:12.824
She's the toad,

38:12.858 --> 38:14.626
I'm not.

38:14.660 --> 38:17.496
Do you understand?

38:18.864 --> 38:20.566
Yes.

38:22.401 --> 38:24.736
Hey, where'd you get
that?

38:24.770 --> 38:27.238
It's a gift
from a client.

38:27.272 --> 38:29.307
Do you know
how to shred?

38:29.341 --> 38:30.976
What?
Shh!

38:31.009 --> 38:34.480
You're going to shred
everything in all these boxes.

38:34.513 --> 38:36.482
Oh. Sure.

38:36.515 --> 38:37.949
What is all this?
Shh!

38:37.983 --> 38:39.651
It's just old files.

38:39.685 --> 38:43.955
Excuse me? Hold on.
You said Temp Joy sent you?

38:43.989 --> 38:45.791
How do I know
that that is even true?

38:45.824 --> 38:48.360
What...
Can you prove it?

38:48.394 --> 38:50.729
You can call Ross
if you want.

38:54.533 --> 38:55.967
It's -- it's...

38:56.001 --> 38:57.135
[Sniffles]

38:57.168 --> 39:00.171
**

39:05.411 --> 39:08.414
**

39:13.919 --> 39:16.021
* Ooh

39:16.054 --> 39:19.057
**

39:24.162 --> 39:27.332
Hi!
What can we do for you?

39:30.602 --> 39:34.172
Hmm.

39:34.205 --> 39:36.207
I'm sorry,
are you okay?

39:36.241 --> 39:39.945
Hi.
Um, I'm sorry, just, uh...

39:39.978 --> 39:41.747
The place looks
really different.

39:41.780 --> 39:43.348
[Chuckles]

39:43.381 --> 39:44.750
You guys did a...

39:44.783 --> 39:46.184
a really nice job.

39:46.217 --> 39:48.053
Thanks. Uh, yeah,
the place was a dump.

39:48.086 --> 39:49.821
You should've seen it.

39:49.855 --> 39:51.690
Yeah. Um...

39:51.723 --> 39:55.060
I'm actually Sean Dudley.

39:55.093 --> 39:58.597
My dad and I
were Dudley & Son.

39:58.630 --> 40:00.331
I'm Son.

40:00.365 --> 40:03.435
Uh, right. Uh...

40:03.469 --> 40:05.170
Listen,
when I said "dump,"

40:05.203 --> 40:07.272
I just meant that the place
had been empty for a long time.

40:07.305 --> 40:10.408
Yeah. [Chuckles]
Yeah, I get it, you know.

40:10.442 --> 40:12.143
Actually,
I'm glad you're here.

40:12.177 --> 40:15.547
Uh, because I wanted to come in,
introduce myself

40:15.581 --> 40:18.850
and, uh, if you don't mind,
offer my services.

40:18.884 --> 40:20.351
Services?

40:20.385 --> 40:23.154
Yeah. Like, inventory,
maintenance, installation.

40:23.188 --> 40:25.156
I got it all wired. Yeah.

40:25.190 --> 40:27.425
You know, I'd be happy to come
on, offer myself as a consultant

40:27.459 --> 40:29.895
and, uh,
when I get off these...

40:29.928 --> 40:32.464
[Chuckles]
...jump back in.

40:32.498 --> 40:34.332
I don't have a vehicle
right now,

40:34.365 --> 40:37.202
but I do know every pool from,
uh, Los Al to Lakewood, so...

40:37.235 --> 40:40.872
Oh. This is our son Booie.
That's his job.

40:40.906 --> 40:43.408
Oh. Hi, Booie.

40:45.477 --> 40:49.515
No, I'd be happy to, uh,
you know, show you the ropes.

40:51.883 --> 40:54.620
Or just help out in here.

40:54.653 --> 40:56.655
That is so nice.
Really.

40:56.688 --> 40:58.356
Uh, but to be honest
with you

40:58.389 --> 41:00.659
and, uh, don't take this
the wrong way --
No. No.

41:00.692 --> 41:03.795
-- hiring you would be like
starting a cruise line

41:03.829 --> 41:06.932
and hiring the captain of
the Titanic to be a consultant.

41:06.965 --> 41:08.466
Right.
You get what I mean?

41:08.500 --> 41:10.035
Uh, yeah. Um...

41:10.068 --> 41:12.370
Greta and I own three
Pool Party locations.

41:12.403 --> 41:15.173
Newport, Irvine,
Aliso Niguel.

41:15.206 --> 41:17.208
We know
how to run a business.

41:17.242 --> 41:20.546
We really feel like this is
an emerging neighborhood.

41:20.579 --> 41:21.847
Emerging from what?

41:21.880 --> 41:24.115
And it gives a chance
for Booie to shine.

41:24.149 --> 41:26.718
He, uh -- he really loves
to clean pools.

41:26.752 --> 41:29.555
Uh, what do you love
about cleaning pools, Booie?

41:29.588 --> 41:31.422
Bitches.

41:31.456 --> 41:32.991
Poolside.

41:33.024 --> 41:35.126
I'm sorry, what?

41:37.729 --> 41:40.498
Oh! [Laughs]

41:40.532 --> 41:42.167
Booie!

41:42.200 --> 41:44.202
Actually, you know, I'm --
I'm glad you stopped by.

41:44.235 --> 41:45.804
We -- We have something
for you.

41:45.837 --> 41:47.138
It, uh --
it came with the lot

41:47.172 --> 41:49.174
when we bought the property
out of receivership.

41:49.207 --> 41:52.143
It's just, uh, you know, some
old ledgers and some Rolodexes.

41:52.177 --> 41:55.446
We were gonna toss it, but,
you know, since you're here.

41:59.851 --> 42:02.854
**

42:11.830 --> 42:13.799
Bill:
Hey, there, Long Beach.

42:13.832 --> 42:18.704
Keep your water crystal-clear
with the help of Dudley Pools.

42:18.737 --> 42:21.372
It's the commercial.
Worried about
keeping your...

42:21.406 --> 42:23.141
Oh, my God.

42:23.174 --> 42:26.144
I haven't seen this
in, like, 20 years?

42:26.177 --> 42:27.946
...and stock up
on everything you need

42:27.979 --> 42:29.514
to keep your home pool
sparkling.

42:29.547 --> 42:31.516
Or hire us,
and we'll make sure

42:31.549 --> 42:34.052
your pool stays ready
for a good time.

42:34.085 --> 42:36.154
It's always summertime...
Mom.

42:36.187 --> 42:38.323
Dad.
Look at those shorts.

42:38.356 --> 42:40.659
...or supplies,
just stop on by.

42:40.692 --> 42:46.431
Or call 562-194-0027.

42:48.900 --> 42:50.902
[Sighs]

42:54.572 --> 42:55.741
Ernie?!

42:57.909 --> 43:00.078
Ernie?!
Are you in there?!

43:01.479 --> 43:03.481
Ernie: Dud?

43:03.514 --> 43:05.050
Hey!

43:05.083 --> 43:07.085
[Chuckles]
There he is.

43:07.118 --> 43:09.354
Yeah, I saw your Caddie
in the driveway,

43:09.387 --> 43:10.622
I thought you were home.

43:10.656 --> 43:12.090
Took a stroll
to the liquor store.

43:12.123 --> 43:15.827
Ah. Well,
it's a beautiful night, huh?

43:17.495 --> 43:19.364
You can see the moon.

43:20.799 --> 43:24.836
I mean, not right now,
but...

43:24.870 --> 43:27.839
it's up there somewhere.

43:27.873 --> 43:30.909
Dud? I'm sorry.

43:30.942 --> 43:34.479
I've been a little AWOL.

43:34.512 --> 43:37.415
I'm glad to hear
you're feeling better.

43:37.448 --> 43:38.416
I feel...

43:38.449 --> 43:40.018
I feel great.

43:42.553 --> 43:44.022
We, uh...

43:44.055 --> 43:45.857
we missed you
at the meeting.

43:45.891 --> 43:47.893
Everybody did.

43:50.028 --> 43:51.897
We need you, man.

43:51.930 --> 43:57.168
We need you, 'cause Scott,
it's like not really, you know,

43:57.202 --> 44:02.407
and, [sighs],
it's your throne.

44:02.440 --> 44:04.575
And you can't just sit back
and let him like --

44:04.609 --> 44:09.280
Scott'll be fine.
Don't get all wrapped up in it.

44:09.314 --> 44:10.916
Okay, fine.

44:10.949 --> 44:12.250
Actually, there was
something else, um,

44:12.283 --> 44:14.052
that I want to
talk to you about.

44:14.085 --> 44:18.089
'Cause there's this family and
they moved into our pool shop --

44:18.123 --> 44:19.657
Listen, man.
Whatever problems you got,

44:19.691 --> 44:22.728
you need to figure it out
on your own, okay?

44:22.761 --> 44:24.329
I gotta demo a pipe threader

44:24.362 --> 44:27.265
for some plumbers up in
Riverside at 7:00 A.M. tomorrow.

44:27.298 --> 44:31.669
Uh, maybe I'll see you
at the Lodge, okay?

44:31.703 --> 44:33.905
Hey. Hey!

44:36.007 --> 44:39.144
Why do you treat me
like a stranger?

44:39.177 --> 44:42.080
You don't return
my phone calls.

44:42.113 --> 44:46.017
I took three buses
to get to the golf course

44:46.051 --> 44:48.253
and you don't even show up.

44:50.021 --> 44:51.556
I mean, is all that stuff
that you said

44:51.589 --> 44:54.025
about being there for me,
was that just bullshit or what?

44:54.059 --> 44:56.962
Dud.
I mean, I --
I was in hospital, Ernie.

44:56.995 --> 44:59.064
I almost died. Again.

44:59.097 --> 45:00.598
And it's like
you don't even care.

45:00.631 --> 45:01.967
That's not it, man.

45:02.000 --> 45:03.601
I got attacked
by a shark,

45:03.634 --> 45:07.172
but it's like you're the one
that's in shock.

45:07.205 --> 45:09.941
What's going on with you,
man?

45:09.975 --> 45:12.210
I mean, something happen
in Santa Barbara?

45:12.243 --> 45:15.180
Did...

45:15.213 --> 45:19.050
Did...some -- Hey? Hey?
We can talk about it.

45:19.084 --> 45:21.719
Ernie, we can talk about
anything,

45:21.753 --> 45:24.022
'cause there's so many great
things going on right with now.

45:24.055 --> 45:25.824
Me and Blaise, we're onto
something big

45:25.857 --> 45:27.759
and I really can't talk
about it, I'm not supposed
to tell you anything.

45:27.793 --> 45:29.727
But you know what, screw it.
I'm gonna tell you right now.

45:29.761 --> 45:30.862
We're gonna complete
the magnum opus.

45:30.896 --> 45:33.131
We're gonna make gold.
No.

45:33.164 --> 45:36.167
I don't want to hear it.

45:36.201 --> 45:39.871
Chasing shadows
like a damn fool.

45:39.905 --> 45:42.373
Never again.

45:42.407 --> 45:44.109
Captain, man.

45:44.142 --> 45:46.644
That shit put me
in a serious hole.

45:46.677 --> 45:48.847
Do you understand me?

45:48.880 --> 45:54.585
All I want is
to get my normal life back.

45:54.619 --> 45:56.221
I -- I got my hopes up,

45:56.254 --> 46:01.893
I got everyone's hopes up,
and it was like poison.

46:01.927 --> 46:05.330
A normal, quiet life,

46:05.363 --> 46:08.233
you'll miss it
once it's gone.

46:08.266 --> 46:09.968
Believe me.

46:10.001 --> 46:14.105
Otherwise, you go down
some crazy path

46:14.139 --> 46:16.808
and there's no coming back.

46:16.842 --> 46:19.945
You'll be stuck in the van
forever.

46:19.978 --> 46:23.982
Every wrong turn
haunting you.

46:25.416 --> 46:26.885
Stuck in a van?

46:26.918 --> 46:28.519
What are you talking about?

46:30.221 --> 46:32.157
[Sighs]

46:32.190 --> 46:34.860
You know what?
Enjoy your normal life.

46:34.893 --> 46:37.228
But guess what?
Got some bad news for ya.

46:37.262 --> 46:38.997
I'm still part of it,
yeah.

46:39.030 --> 46:41.099
So, if you ever need me,

46:41.132 --> 46:43.101
you can just pick up the phone
and call,

46:43.134 --> 46:45.703
because
I'll actually pick up,

46:45.736 --> 46:47.405
'cause I'm your friend.

46:47.438 --> 46:49.807
You dickhead.
And -- And you know what?

46:49.841 --> 46:52.777
I'm not gonna rest until
you're on the throne

46:52.810 --> 46:54.745
and -- and the Lodge

46:54.779 --> 46:57.849
is everything
that it's supposed to be!

46:57.883 --> 47:00.018
Bob:  Ernie, Roto Rudy
wants to know

47:00.051 --> 47:01.920
if you can get to Riverside
by 6:00 A.M.

47:01.953 --> 47:05.423
I told him no problem,
just an FYI.
[  Beep  ]

47:05.456 --> 47:07.893
El Confidente:
Pick up the phone, Ernesto.

47:07.926 --> 47:09.861
We have unfinished business.

47:09.895 --> 47:13.331
Shit got crazy in Comala,
but we have to face up to it.

47:13.364 --> 47:14.866
You can't run.

47:14.900 --> 47:18.169
You left me high and dry and
stole my Goddamn tiger van.

47:18.203 --> 47:20.605
But I'm in a forgiving mood,
Ernesto,

47:20.638 --> 47:23.008
because this
is bigger than you and me.

47:23.041 --> 47:26.044
The scrolls, man.
We're brothers now.

47:26.077 --> 47:28.379
Our bodies are marked
with the truth.

47:28.413 --> 47:31.883
So, you'd better get your ass
back to Mexico.

47:31.917 --> 47:37.288
**

47:37.322 --> 47:39.457
[Door dings]

47:41.359 --> 47:43.261
Hey, Alice?

47:45.596 --> 47:47.732
Hey, Alice,
where are ya?

47:55.206 --> 47:58.209
**

48:02.280 --> 48:05.283
**

48:09.387 --> 48:11.656
* Hope you're free
and better now *

48:11.689 --> 48:14.259
* Your ceiling's gone
[Door dings]

48:14.292 --> 48:16.394
* Hope you're getting out more

48:16.427 --> 48:19.097
* Now the roof ain't on

48:19.130 --> 48:23.601
* Deanimation king who did not
come to fix things *

48:23.634 --> 48:29.540
* Doesn't have to tell you why
[Grunts]

48:29.574 --> 48:32.277
* So kick off your shoes

48:32.310 --> 48:34.312
* And feel some kind of free

48:34.345 --> 48:36.347
What are you doing?

48:36.381 --> 48:38.249
Going into business.

48:39.784 --> 48:41.452
Come on. Come on.

48:41.486 --> 48:45.023
* I do not mean
to interrupt your day *

48:45.056 --> 48:49.060
* But something got me
really carried me away *

48:49.094 --> 48:50.828
Ahh!

48:50.861 --> 48:52.263
Yeah!

48:53.664 --> 48:55.233
Yeah!

48:55.266 --> 48:57.535
**

49:00.738 --> 49:03.741
**

